Smart City Complaint Analysis Report

Introduction

This project analyzes citizen complaints to identify recurring issues, evaluate service efficiency, and improve urban governance.

Objective

To analyze complaint patterns, resolution performance, and citizen satisfaction using data analytics.

Dataset

The dataset contains 2000 complaint records with details such as category, zone, department, priority, status, and resolution delay.

Analysis

- Complaint Category Analysis
- Zone-wise Complaint Analysis
- Department Performance Analysis
- Resolution Time Analysis

Key Findings

- Some complaint categories occur more frequently.
- Certain zones have recurring issues.
- Resolution delays affect citizen satisfaction.
- Department performance varies across services.

Recommendations

- Focus on complaint hotspot zones.
- Reduce resolution delays.
- Improve handling of high-priority complaints.
- Monitor department performance regularly.

Conclusion

The analysis helps city authorities make data-driven decisions to improve public services and citizen satisfaction.
